      "id": 632,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:20",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — activity-completion lifecycle fix in src/db.ts. Build clean (tsc, no errors).\n\n**Changes (3 functions in src/db.ts):**\n\n1. `finishActivity` (line 509) — changed guard from `status = 'in_progress'` to `status != 'aborted'`; all SET fields now use COALESCE so subsequent calls merge without overwriting existing values. Idempotent whether commit fires first or finish_activity fires first.\n\n2. `attachCommitToCurrentActivity` (line 531) — now also sets `status = 'completed'` and `finished_at = COALESCE(finished_at, ?)` alongside commit_sha. Commit step fully closes the activity.\n\n3. `attachCommitToActivityBySlot` (line 552) — same fix as Path A; worktree merge path now also marks the row completed.\n\n**Lifecycle verification:**\n- Normal path: orchestrator commits → activity row gets `status='completed', finished_at=<now>, commit_sha=<sha>` immediately. Subsequent `finish_activity` adds `result_msg_id`; status stays completed (guard allows it, COALESCE doesn't reset finished_at). ✓\n- Reverse path: commit before result_msg_id arrives → activity completed with commit; later `finish_activity` merges result_msg_id. ✓  \n- Worktree merge path: `attachCommitToActivityBySlot` marks completed the same way. ✓\n- Aborted guard: `status != 'aborted'` prevents `finish_activity` from un-aborting a cancelled activity. ✓\n\nNot committed per instructions.",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780680425041,
      "read_at": 1780680428370,
